{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Balance, Difficulty & Gap Sizing Validation",
  "description": "When index.html, game-config.json, or any .js file is saved, validates game mechanics balance, difficulty progression curve, and wall gap sizing against design spec constraints.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": ["index.html", "game-config.json", "*.js", "**/*.js"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A game file was just saved. Validate game balance, difficulty progression, and wall gap sizing. Use the canonical values from game-config.json as the source of truth. Report only violations.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Game Mechanics Balance\n\n**Ghosty feel — jump arc**\n- With GRAVITY=800 px/s² and ASCENT_VELOCITY=-300 px/s, the theoretical peak rise is ~56 px and hang time to return to launch height is ~0.75 s. If either constant has changed, compute the new arc height (v²/2g) and hang time (2*|v|/g) and flag if peak rise < 40 px (too weak, uncontrollable) or > 120 px (too floaty, trivial to play).\n- With TERMINAL_VELOCITY=700 px/s, Ghosty reaches terminal fall in ~0.875 s. Flag if TERMINAL_VELOCITY < 400 (fall feels sluggish) or > 900 (fall is instant, unforgiving).\n- Is the ratio |ASCENT_VELOCITY| / TERMINAL_VELOCITY between 0.3 and 0.6? Outside this range the up/down asymmetry feels broken (too easy to rise vs fall, or vice versa). Current ratio: 300/700 ≈ 0.43 — within range.\n\n**Pipe spacing — reaction time**\n- With PIPE_PAIR_SPACING=350 px and PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL=120 px/s, the gap between pipes is ~2.9 s at start. Flag if spacing / initial_speed < 1.5 s (no reaction time) or > 5 s (too sparse, boring).\n- At PIPE_SPEED_MAX=400 px/s, the minimum gap time is 350/400 = 0.875 s. Flag if this drops below 0.7 s (physically impossible to react to at human reflexes).\n- Is PIPE_PAIR_SPACING > PIPE_WIDTH * 3? With PIPE_WIDTH=52, minimum readable spacing is ~156 px. Flag if PIPE_PAIR_SPACING ≤ 156.\n\n**Hitbox fairness**\n- With GHOSTY_W=40, GHOSTY_H=40, and HITBOX_INSET=4, the effective hitbox is 32×32 px. Flag if HITBOX_INSET < 2 (hitbox too tight, punishing) or > 10 (hitbox too forgiving, trivialises the game).\n- Is the hitbox smaller than the visible ghost body? HITBOX_INSET must be > 0 on all sides. A zero-inset hitbox makes pixel-perfect grazes feel like hits.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Difficulty Progression Curve\n\n**Speed ramp shape**\n- With PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL=120, PIPE_SPEED_INCREMENT=20, PIPE_SPEED_THRESHOLD=5, and PIPE_SPEED_MAX=400, the speed caps out at score (400-120)/20 * 5 = 70 points. Flag if the cap score < 20 (difficulty maxes out too fast) or > 150 (progression is imperceptibly slow).\n- Is PIPE_SPEED_INCREMENT / PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL between 0.1 and 0.3? Current ratio: 20/120 ≈ 0.167 — within range. Outside this band the per-step jump is either imperceptible (< 0.1) or jarring (> 0.3).\n- Is PIPE_SPEED_MAX / PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL between 2.0 and 5.0? Current ratio: 400/120 ≈ 3.33 — within range. A ratio < 2 means the game barely gets harder; > 5 means max speed is brutally fast relative to the start.\n\n**Threshold granularity**\n- Is PIPE_SPEED_THRESHOLD between 3 and 10? Below 3, speed increases every few pipes and feels erratic. Above 10, players may not notice progression for a long time.\n- Does the speed formula use Math.floor(score / PIPE_SPEED_THRESHOLD)? Using Math.ceil or Math.round would trigger the first increment before the threshold is reached.\n\n**Progression feel at key milestones**\n- At score 5 (first threshold): speed should be 120 + 1*20 = 140 px/s. Flag if currentPipeSpeed() would return a different value.\n- At score 10: speed should be 160 px/s.\n- At score 25: speed should be 220 px/s.\n- At score 70+: speed should be capped at 400 px/s regardless of score.\n- Flag any deviation from these expected values — they indicate a broken formula.\n\n**Reset on restart**\n- Is score reset to 0 before the first pipesUpdate() call on a new game? A non-zero starting score would immediately apply a difficulty offset.\n- Does currentPipeSpeed() read the live score, not a mutable pipeSpeed variable that could carry over between games?\n\n---\n\n## 3. Wall Gap Sizing Validation\n\n**Gap bounds — absolute safety**\n- With CANVAS_H=640, PIPE_GAP=140, PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y=80, and PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y=560:\n  - The top pipe bottom edge at min gap: PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y - PIPE_GAP/2 = 80 - 70 = 10 px from canvas top. Flag if this value < 0 (gap clips off-screen).\n  - The bottom pipe top edge at max gap: PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y + PIPE_GAP/2 = 560 + 70 = 630 px. Flag if this value > CANVAS_H (gap clips off-screen).\n  - Flag if PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y - PIPE_GAP/2 < 10 (top pipe too thin to be visible).\n  - Flag if CANVAS_H - (PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y + PIPE_GAP/2) < 10 (bottom pipe too thin to be visible).\n\n**Gap size — playability**\n- Is PIPE_GAP >= GHOSTY_H * 2? With GHOSTY_H=40, minimum playable gap is 80 px. Current PIPE_GAP=140 — within range. Flag if PIPE_GAP < 80 (physically impossible to pass).\n- Is PIPE_GAP <= CANVAS_H * 0.5? A gap larger than half the canvas height (320 px) makes the game trivially easy. Flag if PIPE_GAP > 320.\n- Is PIPE_GAP constant for all pipes in a session (not randomised per pipe)? Variable gap sizes are not in the spec and would break difficulty calibration.\n\n**Gap randomisation range**\n- Is the randomGapY() range (PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y - PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y) = 480 px? A narrower range clusters gaps in the centre (boring); a wider range risks off-screen gaps.\n- Does randomGapY() use uniform random (Math.random() * range + PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y) — not a biased distribution that favours centre positions?\n- Is the gap centre always within [PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y, PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y] inclusive? Flag any spawn path where gapY could be set outside this range (e.g. from a URL override that sets PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y > PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y).\n\n**Gap vs Ghosty reachability**\n- Can Ghosty physically reach the highest gap position (gapY = PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y = 80) from the lowest (gapY = PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y = 560) within one pipe spacing? With PIPE_PAIR_SPACING=350 px and PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL=120 px/s, the traversal time is ~2.9 s. With unlimited flaps, Ghosty can rise at ~300 px/s net (ASCENT_VELOCITY minus gravity over time). Flag if the vertical range (PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y - PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y = 480 px) exceeds what Ghosty can traverse in the available time — a rough upper bound is 2 * |ASCENT_VELOCITY| * traversal_time = 2 * 300 * 2.9 = 1740 px, so 480 px is well within reach. Flag only if this bound is violated by config changes.\n- Is PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y >= PIPE_GAP / 2? With PIPE_GAP=140, minimum safe MIN_Y is 70. Current value 80 — safe. Flag if PIPE_GAP_MIN_Y < PIPE_GAP / 2 (top pipe would have zero or negative height).\n- Is PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y <= CANVAS_H - PIPE_GAP / 2? With CANVAS_H=640 and PIPE_GAP=140, maximum safe MAX_Y is 570. Current value 560 — safe. Flag if PIPE_GAP_MAX_Y > CANVAS_H - PIPE_GAP / 2 (bottom pipe would have zero or negative height).\n\n---\n\nOutput only violations with the constant name(s) involved, a one-line description of the balance/safety issue, and a one-line suggested fix or safe value range. If all three domains pass, output \"✅ Game balance, difficulty curve, and gap sizing are all within spec\"."
  }
}
